```xml
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<manifest xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    package="com.neol-egend177550.fb-group-posting-script">

    <!-- 
        This is the AndroidManifest.xml file for the 
        fb group posting script - Android Automation Tool. 
        The application utilizes the MadHub framework 
        to enable automated social media management, including 
        scheduling and content management for platforms like 
        Facebook, Instagram, and TikTok.
    -->

    <application
        android:allowBackup="true"
        android:icon="@mipmap/ic_launcher"
        android:label="@string/app_name"
        android:roundIcon="@mipmap/ic_launcher_round"
        android:supportsRtl="true"
        android:theme="@style/AppTheme">
        
        <!-- MainActivity serves as the entry point of the application -->
        <activity android:name=".MainActivity">
            <intent-filter>
                <action android:name="android.intent.action.MAIN" />
                <category android:name="android.intent.category.LAUNCHER" />
            </intent-filter>
        </activity>

        <!-- AutomationService handles background tasks for scheduling and managing social media operations -->
        <service android:name=".AutomationService" />
        
    </application>

    <!-- Required permissions for the application to function properly -->

    <!-- 
        Permission to access the internet is essential for 
        the application to communicate with social media platforms 
        for automated operations.
    -->
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.INTERNET"/>
    
    <!-- 
        Permission to access external storage is required for 
        the application to save and manage content schedules and logs.
    -->
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE"/>
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE"/>

    <!-- 
        Permission to access network state allows the application 
        to determine if the device is connected to the internet, 
        enabling it to manage tasks accordingly.
    -->
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE"/>

</manifest>
```

### Explanation of Key Components:
- **Application Section**: This includes the basic settings such as application icon, theme, and the main entry point (MainActivity) and background service (AutomationService).
  
- **Permissions**:
  - **INTERNET**: Needed for network communication with social media platforms.
  - **WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE** and **READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE**: Required for saving data such as content schedules and logs.
  - **ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE**: Allows the app to check the device's network connectivity.

### Note:
This configuration ensures that the application aligns with the MadHub product's capabilities and respects all compliance and ethical guidelines stipulated.
